The President emphasizes the importance of a free press in prosperous and secure societies, as it allows citizens to access information and hold their governments accountable. He acknowledges the risks that journalists take to bring us important stories, and highlights the fact that many journalists have been killed, harassed, threatened, imprisoned, and tortured. The President calls on all governments to protect the ability of journalists to write and speak freely. On the first-ever International Day to End Impunity for Crimes against Journalists, the United States commends the contributions of journalists to freedom and security, and demands accountability for those who have committed crimes against journalists.